This code first uses path.dirname(filePath) to extract the directory path, just as before. Then, to get the filename without its extension, it calls path.basename(filePath, path.extname(filePath)). Here:

- path.basename(filePath) would normally return the filename with its extension.

If you want to get the filename without the extension, you can still use the path module in Node.js. Specifically, you would use the path.basename() function along with the path.extname() function to remove the extension from the filename. Here's how you could do it:

const path = require('path');

// Example file path
const filePath = '/path/to/your/file.txt';

// Get the directory path
const dirPath = path.dirname(filePath);

console.log('Directory Path:', dirPath);
// Get the filename without extension
